Tokens.text: I am 21 years old. My name is Vincent...
I grew up in a big city in Italy.
I enjoyed the easy life, not caring about school. Not caring about friends, or anything.
I soon had to make a choice.
I had to decide what I was going to do with my life.
My life was going down. Everyone else knew what they wanted to do, everyone
My childhood dream has always been to become a rock star.
I was dreaming I'd be famous...
well, that doesn't matter. I could never be famous.
I enjoyed video games, a lot. I'd play hours and hours, day and night.
And I did some programming in school.
I thought that was it. I was going to be a programmer.
I quit. I couldn't stand it.
What am I going to do?

Tokens.innerText: What if I do get a job

Tokens.text: I could get a job. I shouldn't lose hope.
I have finally found the meaning of life.

Tokens.text: It is ok. I am ok. I can find a way. Really
I am alone. But. I do not need anyone. I can live another day.
Maybe the night will fix my bugs.
Wha. Uni-tee? Unity? What is this
Oh, I see. Game development platform... like what I used yesterday! Kind of
Maybe I can create games. Yeah, yeah. Good idea
Oh I know! I'll make a game about a musician. Yes, a rock player
He was in a band, but quit because he was fighting with his mates
And when he was little he wanted to be a programmer
I'll be a game programmer. A... no, a game designer!
I wonder what that elves.exe program was... and why did it help me?
